<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11958&amp;p=135654#p135654</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11958&amp;p=135654#p135654"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NES emulator(s) with inaccurate sound]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11958&amp;p=135654#p135654"><![CDATA[
Yeah, the &quot;static&quot; in FCEUX during play is a result of odd synchronisation/timing issues pertaining to audio/video drivers and/or latency (regardless of what audio card I used (onboard Realtek or an Audigy SE)).  So it makes sense Vsync enable/disable would affect it.  Some of it has been fixed using FCEUX 2.2.3 SVN (I get binaries from emucr.com) and setting Vsync to &quot;Lazy Wait for Vblank&quot; and setting DirectDraw to &quot;No hardware acceleration&quot;.  I have similar synchronisation oddities in other emulators, which is mainly why I use Nestopia when actually wanting to play a NES/FC game, and FCEUX +other emulators solely for debugging/development.  That's just me though.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Mon Oct 27, 2014 8:46 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
